<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She made history as the first ever 'intruder' on the inaugural season of Big Brother Australia in 2001.</p>

<p>But a lot has changed for Anita Bloomfield since then.</p>

<p>Now known by her married name Anita Birges, the 40-year-old has found success as a popular lifestyle influencer specialising in decluttering and organising.</p>

<p>Remember her? She made history as the first ever 'intruder' on the inaugural season of Big Brother Australia in 2001 - but a lot has changed for Anita Bloomfield since then </p>

<p>She also works as a property stylist and consultant, and makes regular appearances on the Today show. </p>

<p>Anita shares tips on how to organise your home with her 16,000 Instagram followers.</p>

<p>The former reality star married husband Ryan earlier this week, and the couple are currently enjoying their honeymoon.</p>

<p>Work it: The 40-year-old has found success as a popular lifestyle influencer specialising in decluttering and organising. Pictured with Richard and Christian Wilkins</p>

<p>Anita entered the Big Brother house on day 38 of the first season, and lasted almost three weeks before being evicted by her fellow housemates.</p>

<p>While she made history as Australia's first ever Big Brother intruder, she wasn't alone.</p>

<p>At the time, she entered the house with fellow intruder Rachel Corbett, who has also carved out a career in the spotlight.</p>

<p>Wedded bliss: The former reality star married husband Ryan earlier this week, and the couple are currently enjoying their honeymoon</p>

<p>Rachel is now a regular panellist on The Project as well as a popular podcaster. </p>

<p>In an interview in 2009, Rachel admitted that she was trying to distance herself from her reality TV past to further her career in television and radio.</p>

<p>'It's part of my past that I've tried to distance myself from, and have so far succeeded,' she told Radio Info.</p>

<p>Big Brother was recently rebooted by Seven with a brand new format and style.  </p>

